# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
 This problem is solved using following steps:
        1>Process parents array and store every parent and its children in a dictionary data structure.Even if node does not have
        children then also it is stored in a dictionary with null children.
        2>Now, we want to traverse the tree in order to calculate score of each node and to calculate the highest score.But,here we are not
        given the root of the tree.So, we will traverse the tree using dictionary data structure created in step 1
        3>Now, DFS is used to traverse the tree recursively.In DFS we do the folllowing:
        i>We visit each node .We get the left node count for that root node,we get right node
        count for that root node.We calculate the count of nodes in that subtree using the formula:left+right+1.
        Lets call it subtree count.This subtree count is used for calculating the score of each node.Also,it is returned to the parent node
        And,parent node calculates its own score from the subtree count of its 2 children.
        ii>After this,we calculate the score of each node.After the current node is removed given tree will be divided into 3 parts: left subtree of current
        node,right subtree of current node and remaining part of the tree after current node is removed.
        We have already calculated the left count and right count in above step.Now, we need to calculate the count of remaining part.
        It is calculated using the formula:total no of nodes in a tree-subtree count
        Thus, score=leftcount*rightCount*remaining count
        iii>Also,We update the maxScore if score so far is greater than maxscore.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
public class Solution {
    Dictionary<int,int[]> children=new Dictionary<int,int[]>();
    long maxScore=0;
    int result=0;

    public long CountNodes(int root,int n)
    {
        long score=0;
        long subtreeCount=0;

        if(root==-1)
        {
            return 0;
        }

        long leftCount=CountNodes(children[root][0],n);
        long rightCount=CountNodes(children[root][1],n);
        subtreeCount=leftCount+rightCount+1;
        long remCount=n-subtreeCount;

        score=(leftCount==0?1:leftCount)*(rightCount==0?1:rightCount);
        score*=remCount==0?1:remCount;

        if(score>maxScore)
        {
            maxScore=score;
            result=1;
        }
        else if(score==maxScore)
        {
            result++;
        }
        return subtreeCount;
    }

    public int CountHighestScoreNodes(int[] parents) 
    {

        int n=parents.Length;
        List<int> lstParents=new List<int>(parents);

        for(int i=0;i<parents.Length;i++)
        {
            int[] arr=new int[2]{-1,-1};
            if(children.ContainsKey(parents[i]))
            {
               children[parents[i]][1]=i;
            }
            else
            {
                arr[0]=i;
                children.Add(parents[i],arr);
            }
        }

        for(int i=0;i<parents.Length;i++)
        {
            int[] arr=new int[2]{-1,-1};
            if(!children.ContainsKey(i))
            {
               children.Add(i,arr);     
            }
        }

        CountNodes(0,n);
        return result;
    }
}
```

