# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Score of a node is the product of subtrees formed by deleting this node 
-> left subtree size * right subtree size * (remaning component above current node)
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Firstly, generate tree
Let x = size of left subtree
y = size of right subtree
score[node] = max(1,x) * max(1,y) * max(1,n-1-x-y);
