# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
- For any node `i`, except root node:
$$score(i) = (n - size_{i}) \space * \space size_{left-child} \space * \space size_{right-child}  $$

- For `root` node:
    $$score(root) = size_{left-child} \space * \space size_{right-child}  $$

Here $$size_{node}$$ = subtree size of node, and `n` is the total number of nodes in the whole tree.


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Use post-order traversal to compute subtree sizes of children.
2. Compute score for each node using above formula.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:  $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

