# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We can get the size of each subtree by counting number of nodes under that specific index.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Construct our tree, my impl is using a map(key: parent, value: children)

Post Order traverse the tree record the size of subtree using a `table` array

**Use `long` to mark subtree size and product**

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n)

# Code
```java
class Solution {
    public int countHighestScoreNodes(int[] parents) {
        int count = parents.length;
        Map<Integer, List<Integer>> map = new HashMap<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < count; i ++) {
            map.put(i, new ArrayList<>());
        }

        for (int i = 1; i < count; i ++) {
            int parent = parents[i];
            map.get(parent).add(i);
        }

        long[] table = new long[count];
        traverse(0, map, table);
        int result = 0;
        long max = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < count; i ++) {
            long parentCount = i == 0 ? 1 : count - table[i];
            long product = 1L;
            if (map.get(i).size() == 0) {
                product = 1L * parentCount;
                if (product == max) {
                    result ++;
                } else if (product > max) {
                    max = product;
                    result = 1;
                }
            } else if (map.get(i).size() == 1) {
                product = parentCount * table[map.get(i).get(0)];
                if (product == max) {
                    result ++;
                } else if (product > max) {
                    max = product;
                    result = 1;
                }
            } else {
                product = parentCount * table[map.get(i).get(0)] * table[map.get(i).get(1)];
                if (product == max) {
                    result ++;
                } else if (product > max) {
                    max = product;
                    result = 1;
                }
            } 
        }
        System.out.println(max);
        return result;
    }


    private long traverse(int root, Map<Integer, List<Integer>> map, long[] table) {
        if (!map.containsKey(root) || map.get(root).size() == 0) {
            table[root] = 1L;
            return 1L;
        }
        if (map.get(root).size() == 1) {
            long childCount = traverse(map.get(root).get(0), map, table);
            table[root] = childCount + 1;
            return table[root];
        } 

        long left = traverse(map.get(root).get(0), map, table);
        long right = traverse(map.get(root).get(1), map, table);

        table[root] = left + right + 1;
        return table[root];
    }
}
