# Intuition
1. Map parents to their children.
2. Go through the children recursively to find the sizes so you can calculate score
3. Score = product of size[children] - size[parent] - 1
4. Find max in score array and its frequency

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(N*2^M) where N = number of parents in tree; M = number of children

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(N) where N = number of entries or parents in this case

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int countHighestScoreNodes(int[] parents) {
        int n = parents.length;
        long[] scores = new long[n];
        int[] sizes = new int[n];
        Map<Integer, List<Integer>> parent_to_child = new HashMap<>();
        Arrays.fill(scores, -1);
        for(int i=1;i<n; i++){
            parent_to_child.computeIfAbsent(parents[i], k -> new ArrayList<>());
            parent_to_child.get(parents[i]).add(i);
        }
        for(Map.Entry entry : parent_to_child.entrySet())
            getScores(scores, (int)entry.getKey(), parent_to_child, sizes, new int[1]);
        long max=Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for(long i : scores)
            max = Math.max(max,i);
        int count=0;
        for(long i : scores)
            if(i==max)count++;
        return count;
    }
    private int getScores(long[] scores, int key, Map<Integer, List<Integer>> parent_to_child, int[] sizes, int[] res){
        if(scores[key]!=-1)
            return 0;
        if(parent_to_child.get(key) == null) {
            scores[key] = scores.length-1;
            return 0;
        }
        for(int child : parent_to_child.get(key)){
            res[0] = getScores(scores, child, parent_to_child, sizes, res);
            int temp = sizes[key];
            sizes[key] += sizes[child] + 1;
            int diff = sizes[key] - temp;
            if(temp==0) temp=1;
            scores[key] = temp * diff;
        }
        int remainingNodes = scores.length - sizes[key] - 1 == 0 ? 1 : scores.length - sizes[key] - 1;
        scores[key] *= remainingNodes;
        return sizes[key];
    }
}
```

