# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

the approach is pretty straight forward we make a tree using the parents array and do a DFS and calculate number of nodes in each subtree. 

# calculation of Score
Score = left * right * (n-left-right-1)

where left, right and (n-left-right-1) is not 0.
left = nodes in left subtree
right = nodes in right subtree
n = total nodes

# Code
```
class Solution {
    long mx = 0;
    int cnt = 0;

    public int countHighestScoreNodes(int[] parents) {
        int n = parents.length;
        int tree[][] = new int[n][2];

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
