**# Intuition
WE WILL STORE ALL NODES CONNECTED WITH EACH NODE IN A MAP OF INT AND VECTOR.AND IF WE KNOW SIZE OF EACH SUBTREE BY PRECOMPUTATION THEN ONLY WE WOULD HAVE TO MULTIPLY ALL THE STORED NODES' SIZES AND DO COMPARISON. 

# Approach
WE WILL DO SIMPLE DFS AND STORE THE SIZE OF EACH NODE AND BY GIVEN ARRAY WE CAN EASILY MAKE PARENT CHILD RELATIONS IN A MAP (unordered_map<int,vector<int>> v)

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
WE ARE TRAVERING PARENT ARRAY AND DOING DFS SO TIME COMPLEXITY WILL BE O(N),WHERE N IS NUMBER OF NODES

- Space complexity:
WE ARE STORING EACH NODES SIZES AND EACH NODES CHILDREN ,SO SPACE COMPLEXITY WILL BE O(N)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
 unordered_map<int,vector<int>> v;
 unordered_map<int,int> s;

 int func(int x,int pr){

     for(auto&it:v[x]){
         if(it==pr) continue;
         int y=func(it,x);
         s[x]+=y; // STORING SIZE OF EACH NODE IN MAP
     }
     s[x]++;
     return s[x];
 }
    int countHighestScoreNodes(vector<int>& parents) {

        int size=parents.size();
         // MAKING PARENT CHILD RELATIONS
        for(int i=1;i<size;i++){
               v[parents[i]].push_back(i);
               v[i].push_back(parents[i]);
        }
        func(0,-1);

        // FOR STORING EACH SCORE
        vector<long long int> ans;

        //REMOVING VERTEX ONE BY ONE
        for(auto&it:v){
            long long int ml=1;
